    <h2 class="h2">You're consumed by the work</h2>
    <div style="max-width:56ch">
      <p>The job in front of you, the client who needs an answer now, the fire that started this morning. So you handle it — by hand, again, like last week and the week before.</p>
      <p>Some days the work isn't the fire. Some days you have to work on the firetruck, so it's ready when the fire comes. Some days you install the smoke alarm, so the fire doesn't start at all. That's the work that actually changes things — and it's the work that never gets done, because you're too busy surviving the week to build the thing that would end the fight.</p>
      <p>It's your job to see it before it happens. But being ahead means doing more work, and you're already past full. That's the trap: the thinking that would get you out is the thing you have no time to do.</p>
