<section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
  <div class="se">The Assessment</div>
  <h2 class="h2">We don't do free</h2>
  <div class="rule"></div>
  <p>Free means you have time to give away. Our time is valuable — and so is yours. If you're looking for something for nothing, we don't have anything for you.</p>
  <p>But if you're willing to invest the one resource you can't get back — your time — then we'll meet you there. You bring the time and the seriousness. We bring the work, at no cost to you, long before anyone talks about money.</p>
  <h3 class="h3">How the Assessment works</h3>
  <p>It starts with a conversation. A set time, forty-five minutes — not a sales call dressed up as a favor. The first session exists to expose the real problem, which is almost never the one you came in naming. Most engagements don't stop at one; four to eight sessions is common, because digging into how a business actually runs takes more than one sitting.</p>
  <h3 class="h3">Good tools pay for themselves</h3>
  <p>We don't build tools. We build effective solutions. A home health agency we worked with was drowning in compliance — the state requires documents on file and proof of due diligence on every hire. We built them automated intelligence backed by real tracking: an interface that kept them compliant and gave their staff a clear path. The tool paid for itself in time, in stress, and in audits that stopped being a crisis.</p>
</div></section>

<section class="section wash"><div class="wrap narrow">
  <div class="se">Who we are</div>
  <h2 class="h2">Built by operators, not advisors</h2>
  <div class="rule"></div>
  <p>Before Bussey and Bussey, we built White Shovel — a landscape design firm — and the software behind it. We built the systems and the design tools ourselves, and they turned an ordinary salesperson into a capable designer. The efficiency was real enough that we could hand homeowners a finished design for free and still win the work. Then we sold it.</p>
  <p>We've spent the years since building software and tools for service companies across industries. Research is the foundation of good development, and ours is solid. We're often surprised by what people assume can't be done with AI or software — and rarely surprised by what turns out to be possible once someone digs. We find the solutions. We bring them to you.</p>
</div></section>

